text: MOAStream source now supports chunking, generating Instances instead of Instance objects. Training/evaluation speed-ups of up to 20x!
Work on incubator module for tumblr has commenced.
SpreadSheet file viewer now "remembers" the custom reader setups for the "open recent..." menu item.
The adams-moa module now uses the new MOA 2013.11 release.
Visualizing tweets on map using GeoTools: http://t.co/G8CWFrqvPx
I added a video to a @YouTube playlist http://t.co/29k8IuhcFp Displaying tweets using GeoTools
Extending the expression parsers/spreadsheet formulas with custom functions: https://t.co/TnmwhofyuJ
ADAMS now requires Java 7 (source + target).
Video on time series support available: http://t.co/sLKbY6aYTW
New release available: 0.4.4. https://t.co/S914zFr7Cs
Getting ready for making a release  - hopefully tomorrow.
Subversion repo structure changed - https://t.co/DkhJrgs2Yt
File choosers now have bookmarks support for directories. Image file choosers also sport a preview thumbnail now.
Added basic functionality for creating charts in the spreadsheet viewer, using flows as backend.
SelectObjects and WekaSelectObjects sources allow you to interactively select objects from arbitrary class hierarchies and broadcast them.
Added support for overlay visualization to SequencePlotter. Overlays get generated with PlotProcessor actor, eg LOWESS, Savitzky-Golay.
Data Mining with Weka MOOC has commenced! http://t.co/bv5HLve0tS
The Spreadsheet Viewer tool now allows you to run SQL-like queries on the current tab, creating a new tab with the transformed spreadsheet.
The SpreadSheetQuery transformer sports a simple SQL-like query language for processing spreadsheets: SELECT, UPDATE, DELETE
Added support for processing Java properties files: read/write of files, get/set of properties, display as table.
RT @WekaMOOC: Enrolment opens for "Data Mining with Weka" - new #MOOC from @Waikato. http://t.co/SCgrUWnriz #WekaMOOC #Weka #datamining
Basic OCR support is now available using a wrapper around tesseract (needs to be installed).
Timeseries module - https://t.co/fglHiB4AC5
Processing XML, HTML and JSON - https://t.co/G94vbgToDR
It's been quite on the update front, but only due to the website requiring an upgrade. We're back! :-)
New release 0.4.3 available! https://t.co/Ymw6KzGN9M
adams-imaging: the ImageMetaData transformer extracts EXIF/IPTC meta data from an image and generates a spreadheet from the information.
JavaExec standalone allows you to launch JVM process with same or augmented classpath. Allows post-processing of stdout/stderr output.
Emailing support rewritten: CreateEmail, SendEmail, EmailFileReader, EmailFileWriter, EmailViewer instead of just Email sink.
TwitterListener source working again, after moving to twitter4j 3.0.3. Added global preferences dialog for keys/secrets.
Complete rewrite of documentation generators for flows: DocBook and LateX. Newly added: XHTML.
Added reader for Gnumeric workbooks. Excel, ODF and Gnumeric readers/writers now support reading/writing of multiple sheets at once.
Added experimental support for loading SQL dumps as spreadsheets.
The SpreadSheetMerge transformer allows you to merge multiple sheets, either simple side-by-side or via row-matching using an ID column.
Model files get automatically compressed/decompressed using gzip if the extension is .model.gz instead of .model alone.
Improved flow editor UI experience: keeps expanded state now when applying flow processors, eg renaming global actors or events.
Added transformers for evaluating WEKA clusterers (cross-validation, test, train/test).
WekaMergeInstances can process weka.core.Instances objects now directly. So far, transformer used file names as input.
Email-handling just got easier with the introduction of a simple Address Book frontend and easier editing of email addresses in the GUI.
BinaryFileReader transformer and various byte-related conversions allow you to read in (and process) binary files now.
simplified quick info string generation: adams.core.QuickInfoHelper. Reworked all existing methods. Probably screwed up some in process.
It is now possible to attach variables to options consisting of arrays, eg the "recipients" of the Email sink.
Just added WEKA converters that wrap around any ADAMS spreadsheet reader/writer: SpreadSheetLoader/Saver.
experimental feature: Database/FTP/SMTP/SSHConnection standalones allow prompting for password at runtime if no password provided.
The new SMTPConnection standalone allows overriding of global Email setup in flows.
Breakpoint actor now uses tabbed pane, rather than separate dialogs: https://t.co/fUHfvjncXm
Basic support for processing/displaying JSON files/objects is now available in the adams-core module.
Added experimental locale support: eg allows importing CSV files in one locale and saving in another locale.
Added generic Draw transformer to adams-imaging module. Supports setting pixels, drawing lines, rectangles, ovals, text and images.
Added COUNTIF method to spreadsheet formulas. SpreadSheetAddFormulaColumn/Row conversions add user-supplied formulas to spreadsheets.
I added a video to a @YouTube playlist http://t.co/EqCdoWl7qs Classifier evaluation: from simple to complex
Video available for turning a simple cross-validation flow into a complex, flexible one - http://t.co/Z5aGdeudeh
Cross-validation: from simple to complex! http://t.co/EqCdoWl7qs
Groovy updated to 2.1.1, Jython to 2.5.3 and WEKA to 3.7.9.
ADAMS is now listed on Softpedia: http://t.co/SXRuZG9CFC
New release 0.4.2 available! Boasts experimental R integration and WEKA webservice - https://t.co/oxknU97S9m
Video demonstrating the WEKA webservice capability. Allows non-Java clients to utilize WEKA functionality. http://t.co/uC6aRDSZkv
Connecting to R from within the workflow using Rserve. http://t.co/IiV4KB6E
Just added support for writing conversion schemes (adams.data.conversion) using Jython and Groovy. See examples in respective manual.
The SpreadSheetConvertCells/TransformCells transformers allow you to convert cells with a conversion/global transformer.
Thanks to Rserve, you can now process data in the flow using R scripts: adams-r module (RStandalone, RSource, RTransformer, RSink).
Spreadsheets now support basic formulas, offering functions like sum or average that work on cell ranges and other mathematical ones.
The adams-weka-webservice now offers parameter optimization using the MultiSearch meta-classifier on the server-side.
Handling very large CSV files - https://t.co/3y2dKNVM
Lookup tables/dictionaries support - https://t.co/1HAyPkd1
Just added a new video on how to use the new flow execution listeners: http://t.co/SOkJLmfl
I added a video to a @YouTube playlist http://t.co/kJmAkuDN Flow Execution Listeners
Flow Execution Listeners: http://t.co/kJmAkuDN via @YouTube
The new flow execution listeners allow you to monitor a flow more closely, eg how much time an actor consumed or how often it got executed.
Added interactive SelectDateTime source actor, allowing user to choose date/time, date or time.
Just in time for Xmas, a new release of ADAMS: 0.4.1 - you can get it from here: https://t.co/kpODNAIk
With new built-in sqlite support, you can now import multiple spreadsheets into DB, create joins and export new spreadsheets. On-the-fly!
The Spreadsheet file viewer now allows you to apply spreadsheet-specific transformers
Another spreadsheet overhaul for faster processing and higher memory efficiency: https://t.co/YUleAhtQ
Fixed bug in GOE editor class adams.gui.goe.FileEditor: "Select" action got ignored. https://t.co/af6EBsKE
SpreadSheet objects use different internal representation now in order to conserve memory.
The AggregateSpreadSheet conversion of the adams-spreadsheet module lets you generate aggregates of rows, like sum, average, stdev.
FFmpeg wrapper now available from the adams-imaging module. E.g., you can create movies from (enumerated) screenshots using this actor.
Spreadsheet support has been extended to support date/time. Viewer tool can filter data now.
The adams-moa module now has an additional tutorial on using MOA and ADAMS, thanks to Albert Bifet.
Added transformer for sorting spreadsheets: SpreadSheetSort. Can use arbitrary number of columns, descending or ascending.
I added a video to a @YouTube playlist http://t.co/42r3DmFQ Cross-validating a classifier
I added a video to a @YouTube playlist http://t.co/h8MpGqTS Hello World
I uploaded a @YouTube video http://t.co/42r3DmFQ Cross-validating a classifier
I uploaded a @YouTube video http://t.co/h8MpGqTS Hello World
More spreadsheet support: SpreadSheetRemoveRow/Column for removing rows/cols, SpreadSheetDifference for difference between spreadsheets.
Basic heat map support just got added: adams-heatmap
Added new "tab" to flow editor: Clipboard. Allows storing of arbitrary number of actors during a session. Offers preview of stored actors.
The screenshots in the adams-moa and adams-weka modules have been updated.
Added some more example flows in the adams-moa module, mainly comparing performances of classifiers.
How to use filters on MOA data streams https://t.co/RVtak3HT
Added experimental Explorer GUI to adams-weka module: uses menus instead of buttons.
ADAMS is now listed on Ohloh: https://t.co/1o4JDc29
Added attribute selection support to the adams-weka module.
Fixed display bug in SpreadSheetTableModel with fixed number of decimals for numbers less than. Affected SpreadSheetDisplay sink.
ADAMS compiles successfully under 1.7.0_09.
Deprecation of WekaClassifer/Clusterer, MOAClassifier/Clusterer. https://t.co/wLOw95Cc
Titus Brown on "Automated testing and research software". http://t.co/O6G4Z89T
SpreadSheetAnonymize - if you need to anonymize sensitive columns in your spreadsheets.
TabView - same functionality as GridView, but uses a tabbed pane instead of a grid layout.
Cross-validation of WEKA classifiers in the flow can take advantage of multi-core machines now.
Added quick overview on actors, conditions, etc to manual of adams-weka module.
WekaInstancesAppend appends multiple datasets, creating one large one (one-after-other). WekaInstancesMerge creates side-by-side dataset.
"Dataset compatibility" is a new tool in the adams-weka module that can check multiple datasets on their compatibility (WEKA is picky!)
Introduced "atomic execution". User can protect sub-flows of certain actors, like Tee, Trigger, Branch, using flag "finishBeforeStopping".
Flow editor can now generate side-by-side diff between current flow and next undo step. Useful check after applying actor processes.
Just added a little graphical tool for analyzing the console output, making it easier locating errors: Console output analyzer
Files (e.g., datasets or models) can be directly previewed from within the Flow, right-click on a file and select "Open in preview browser".
I uploaded a @YouTube video http://t.co/6v7AmIsq Raspbery Pi running a webservice
I added a video to a @YouTube playlist http://t.co/v896Vgqy ADAMS on Raspberry Pi
Just fixed example flow download, since not all examples were included. Also re-enabled snapshots. https://t.co/kpODNAIk
I uploaded a @YouTube video http://t.co/v896Vgqy ADAMS on Raspberry Pi
ADAMS is now listed on COSI http://t.co/GMEfN0lP and http://t.co/4Q30Y9ER http://t.co/KQNWuSXU
ADAMS is now publicly available as open-source (GPLv3). Check out homepage for downloads and more: https://t.co/n1qpYRqv
ADAMS https://t.co/n1qpYRqv presented at ECML-PKDD 2012 by @joavanschoren #ecmlpkdd
I uploaded a @YouTube video http://t.co/iomI4b4 LEIA: Vehicle Detection
I uploaded a @YouTube video http://t.co/qQQcIqM LEIA: Bridge Vibration
New standalone actor: GridView. Allows combining any graphical actors into a single grid layout.
Arrays can now get created on-the-fly with the NewArray source. SetArrayElement allows use of storage items now, too.
Added support for diff'ing in ADAMS: unified, side-by-side, brief. As well as displaying side-by-side diff graphically.
I've uploaded an @YouTube video http://t.co/9LBZVZb Interactive spectral analysis
ADAMS finally Maven conform: proper separation of classes and resources! :-) New developer version is 0.4.0-SNAPSHOT

Added experimental support for attaching global actors to options: @{global:actorname}. Kind of multiple inputs.
I've uploaded an @YouTube video http://t.co/WEAore3 GC-MS Sample type checker
Started youtube channel for ADAMS: http://t.co/a7Jvd4F
New release is out, incl inline editing in GOE: 0.3.31. Developer artifactId is now 0.3.32-SNAPSHOT.
Flow editor can export flows as images or print them on a printer now as well.
StringReplace now supports Java character sequence replacement; unfortunately, change breaks -all option (using enum instead of bool opts).
Just committed experimental "inline editing" in the GOE for variable names, regexps, math expressions, etc. Less clicking. :-)
Released another bugfix release 0.3.29, new developer version is 0.3.30-SNAPSHOT.
After adding maven support to WEKA, published most of packages on maven central. Waiting for Mark to release new version to complete switch.
Removed jmathplot dependency and pushed out new released 0.3.27. New developer version is 0.3.28-SNAPSHOT.
Just pushed out a new release: 0.3.26. Development version is now 0.3.27-SNAPSHOT
Just upgraded the adams-twitter module: implemented OAuth and sink for tweeting status updates.
The process of open sourcing ADAMS is finally underway.
